DevOps Notes

Vision Control Systems
GIT GIT-HUB GIT-LAB
Two types of Version Control Systems :- 
 - Centralized
 - Decentralized
 Best tool for version control system is GIT


Continuous Intergration -: CI
 - multiple integrations at a time: Bug fix, improve software quality, faster time of code release
 - Jenkins is the most used for CI

Continuous Testing
 - Executing by automation with immediate results/feedback
 - All Codes should be executable
 - Verify Code works as expected
 - DevOps automates the process using tools:
   1. Junit
   2. Selenium

Continuous Deployment
Differents bt C Delivery and C Deployment
 - C Delivery is a manual process
 - C Deployment is automated process

Continous Monitoring
 - Monitor resources/infrastructure
   * Software functionality
   * Components/Hardware usage
   * Increases Visibility for risk and performance
   * Tools used for monitory:
    1. Nagios
    2. Splunk
    3. Kibana
    4. Grafana


Infrastructure as a Code
 - Provisioned and managed using codes for software development
 - Version control 
 - Continuous integration

SDLC - Software Development Life Cycle
 - Planning
 - Defining
 - Designing
 - Building
 - Testing
 - Deployment

1.Core:
• git init
• git clone: The git clone command is used to create a copy of a Git repository on your local machine. It makes a duplicate of the remote repository, including all of its branches, commit history, and files.
• git add
• git commit
• git status
• git diff
• git checkout
• git reset
• git log
• git show
• git tag
• git push
• git pull

2.Branching:
• git branch
• git checkout -b
• git merge
• git rebase
• git branch --set-upstream-to
• git branch --unset-upstream
• git cherry-pick

3.Merging:
• git merge
• git rebase

4.Stashing:
